    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-10T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="699"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d699">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856E.00/2–1047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-10T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 10, 1947—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Rejection [of] Dutch Government interpretation Linggadjati Agreement by
                    Indonesian Cabinet, which declares such interpretation as violation original
                    agreement, viewed with concern by Foreign Office official charged with Indies
                    matter, who says “critical situation” thus created. Informant added Government
                    awaiting official views Republican Government and report from Commission General
                    before deciding its future policy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hornbeck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
